{
  "stem": "2581.4",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they had assumed that these two children were killed.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Now, who would have killed these children?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The Jews.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So that was the reason for the pogrom.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The point I'm trying to make, at the end of that program, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] they are interviewing a priest, a Catholic priest.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they're asking him, is it true that the Jews are using gentiles' children blood for their ritual needs?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In this case, was to strengthen the weakened people that came back from the concentration camp and from Russia.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Not for maztahs, but to give them injection-- blood injections from these children.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So his answer was years ago, it was a fact.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Today, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So this is what is happening to this very day.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We're not talking about 20 years ago, you know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And, of course, we could talk forever about the-- my fights in Poland, or my reactions in Poland when I came across anti-Semitic-- Can I ask you, just before we end, some questions about life here?",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Do you have-- you've got how many grandchildren?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We have not enough, but six.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[LAUGHTER] Six grandchildren.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, what I would like to say to them is that, with all their might, they should fight against hate and prejudice.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because, as we see now, what hate and prejudice can lead to.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We don't have to look far.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We have Oklahoma City and other places.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But it's so important that they should fight it as Jewish people and as an American citizen.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because this country has been very good to us.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
